Explanation:
1. Initialize cost array and set all '?' to 0 and other characters to 1.
2. Iterate through the string and for each '?', find the minimum cost among characters before it.
3. Replace the '?' with the minimum cost character found in step 2.
4. Return the substring from index i to i + minCost.

This solution has a time complexity of O(n), where n is the length of the string. The space complexity is O(1) since we only use a single integer array for cost. The energy implications are low since the algorithm only performs a constant number of operations per character.

